sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1532
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Thermal Hysteresis (Antifreeze) Protein (variant YL1) with 8-His tag with secretion tag and GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a thermal hysteresis (antifreeze) protein with an 8-His tag for protein purification. It has up to 100 times the specific activity of fish antifreeze proteins. There are four variants of the protein (YL1-4). This is variant YL1. There is a secretion tag, and a portion of the sequence causes the cell to secrete GFP as well to measure the activity of the promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sarah Allred
